<p class="MsoNormal">All,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">I have an mpi-based program that has a master process that acts as a &#8216;traffic cop&#8217; in that it hands out work to child processes.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">I want to be able to dynamically throttle how many child processes are in use at any given time.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">For instance, if I start it with &#8220;mpirun -n 512&#8221; I could send a signal to tell it to only use 256 of them for a bit and then tell it to scale back up. The upper limit being the number of processes mpirun was launched with.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Has anyone done anything like this? Maybe a better way to do it?
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Basically my program is crunching through a large text file, examining each line for various things.
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Thanks in advance for any insight,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
